Package com.iontrading.mkv

Class MkvCustomStatsTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.iontrading.mkv.MkvCustomStatsTable
  • @Keep
@KeepPublicClassMemberNames
public class MkvCustomStatsTable
extends Object
    This class provides a container for custom statistics of a given category. To get a reference to a specific table, use the MkvCustomStatsManager.

    References to this objects can be used to send non-standard performance indicators to the Daemon Master, to be capture using the Diagnostics product.

    See Also:
    MkvCustomStatsManager, MkvCustomStatsListener

    • Method Detail

      • extendTable

        public MkvCustomStatsTable extendTable​(String category)
        This method changes the property of the custom stats table. It specifies that this table will be used as extension for another category information.

        This is the usual case when the Custom Application wants to publish additional columns for standard statistics table, like Components or Connections tables.

        The category of a table identifies the logical statistics group it refers to.

        Parameters:
        category - The mnemonic name for the statistics group you want to extend
        Returns:
        This object

      • addKeyFields

        public MkvCustomStatsTable addKeyFields​(String[] keyFields)
        This method changes the property of the custom stats table. It specifies that this table will be used as a custom drill-down for another category information.

        This is the usual case when the Custom Application wants to publish additional statistics that can be accessed through a navigation from the parent table.

        The category of a table identifies the logical statistics group it refers to. The key fields are the field names that will be concatenated to create the primary key of this table.

        Parameters:
        keyFields - The field names that will be concatenated to create the primary key of this table
        Returns:
        This object

      • send

        public void send​(MkvSupply data,
                 long timestamp,
                 long reportTime)
        This method can be used to report the new values of the custom statistics to the Daemon Master, to be captured using the Diagnostics product. These values must be manually associated with a pre-calculated timestamp, and a pre-calculated report time, useful when user wants to do specify the time of the sampling and the time of the reporting.
        Parameters:
        data - The MkvSupply object associated to the values of the custom statistics indicators
        timestamp - The timestamp related this sampling
        reportTime - The timestamp related to the when the statistics was produced

      • send

        public void send​(MkvSupply data,
                 long timestamp)
        This method can be used to report the new values of the custom statistics to the Daemon Master, to be captured using the Diagnostics product. These values must be manually associated with a pre-calculated timestamp, and the engine attaches to the sampling the current report time.
        Parameters:
        data - The MkvSupply object associated to the values of the custom statistics indicators
        timestamp - The timestamp related this sampling

      • send

        public void send​(MkvSupply data)
        This method can be used to report the new values of the custom statistics to the Daemon Master, to be captured using the Diagnostics product. The engine automatically attaches a fresh timestamp and the current report time to the sampling.
        Parameters:
